Source: mixctl
Section: sound
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Gregory Huber <greghuber@users.noreply.github.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), cargo, rustc, libpipewire-0.3-dev, libclang-dev, pkg-config
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/plohkoon/mixctl

Package: mixctl
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, pipewire
Description: Linux userspace controller for USB audio mixers
 mixctl manages audio routing through PipeWire with an input/output matrix
 model, a CLI, TUI, and desktop UI. Device adapters connect hardware
 controllers (Beacn Mix, GoXLR, MIDI controllers, etc.) via a plugin SDK.

Package: mixctl-beacn
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, mixctl
Description: Beacn Mix Create device adapter for mixctl
 Device adapter connecting the Beacn Mix Create USB audio mixer hardware
 (4 dials, 11 buttons, 800x480 LCD, RGB LEDs) to the mixctl daemon.
